RACE.FOOTNOTES: KINGMEISTER was forwardly placed in the early running, tracked the decent fractions while well placed through the backstretch run, loomed along the second turn, confronted the pacesetter nearing the quarter marker, steadily advanced on IL CAPITANO into upper stretch, overtook that rival at the furlong marker and assumed command under steady urging, kept to task to deep stretch and drew clear in the final stages. JACKS OUTLAW settled off of the decent early pace while saving ground, moved closer along the second turn and saved all of the ground to the quarter marker, ran evenly to mid-stretch, was outkicked by the winner in deep stretch and just held for second at the finish. OUR SILVER OAK settled in the second flight early on, tracked the pace while outside of a rival through the backstretch run, gained ground two wide on the far turn, was roused three wide for the drive, ran evenly to the furlong marker, lacked the needed late response and was outfinished in deep stretch, just missed for second and held for third. TABLE FOR TEN was unhurried in the early stages, saved all of the ground to the second turn, offered a mild late rally in the drive and missed for the minor awards. IL CAPITANO showed early speed and assumed command leaving the break, was a bit keen into the first turn and continued to be a bit hard to handle into the backstretch run, set decent fractions while on a clear lead to the half-mile pole, was confronted by KINGMEISTER nearing the quarter marker, held the winner at bay to mid-stretch, was collared by KINGMEISTER at the furlong marker and gave way in the late stages.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERFORMATIVE broke alertly then took back to stalk the fast early pace, advanced along the bend and pressed BOLD TALKER to the quarter marker, drew to even terms with that rival into upper stretch, took command nearing the furlong marker, drew off into deep stretch and was ridden out in the final stages to be much the best. WAKES AND WEDDINGS tracked the fast early pace while three wide, inched closer approaching the quarter pole, was no match for the winner in the stretch and ran on in the final sixteenth to be best of the rest. BOLD TALKER showed good early speed and took command in the opening stages, set a quick pace into the turn, was pressured by PERFORMATIVE to the quarter marker, met that foe's bid into upper stretch, gave way inside of the furlong marker and was outfinished for second, while clear of the rest for third. THECHIEFHASTRICKS hopped at the start then lost his path soon after the break and was away slowly, chased from the inside along the turn and did not factor in the drive. UPDRAFT chased the solid early pace, raced outside of a rival to the quarter marker, dropped back into upper stretch and tired.

DERRYGOOLIN was allowed to settle, maintained her position through the backstretch run, raced two wide into the far turn, gained ground nearing the quarter marker and waited a bit behind runners approaching the top of the lane, was roused four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, lacked the needed late response and was outfinished for second, while clear in the end for third. SWALL settled in the second flight in the early stages, tracked the solid pace while outside of a rival through the backstretch run, mounted a three wide bid on the second turn, could not sustain that bid into the stretch and weakened in the drive. CALLHERCONTESSA was prominent in the early running, disputed the quick pace into the first turn then took back to prompt the pacesetter through the backstretch run, kept attendance to LADYWEARSTHERING to the quarter marker, chased the winner to mid-stretch and gave way in the final stages. EM N HOLL'S FIESTA stalked the quick early pace from the inside, tracked the speed while inside of a rival through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground to the far turn, steadied off of a tiring rival's heels in upper stretch, could not keep pace to the furlong pole and tired in the final stages. NOBLE HEARTED settled off of the fast early pace, raced outside of a rival through the backstretch run, was steered three wide along the turn, could not keep pace into upper stretch and did not threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOL MOUNTAIN LAD broke out slightly at the break, was first into stride then ceded the lead to AWESOME SUMMER passing the five furlong marker, shifted out to the two path at the half-mile pole then moved to challenge the leader on the turn, battled that stubborn rival down the length of the stretch, gained a slight advantage inside the sixteenth and held on to the wire. AWESOME SUMMER bumped after the break with LMLOOKNFORMISCHIEF, got into stride then set a comfortable pace with COOL MOUNTAIN LAD in close pursuit, responded when challenged with three furlongs to go, held on gamely to a slight lead in the final sixteednth but was bested in the final yards. LMLOOKNFORMISCHIEF broke out at the start, making contact with AWESOME SUMMER, then steadied, giving his two rivals a head start, fell behind in the early going then was in striking distance going into the turn, drifted out through the turn losing ground on the leaders then was four or five wide into the stretch and was unable to threaten.

ZAFFERANA took back off of the early pace, tracked the decent fractions while outside of a rival through the backstretch run, made a steady advance while two wide along the far turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and bested the rest. NOT NOW I'M BIZZIE settled along the rail in the early running, saved all of the ground to the far turn, improved position nearing the quarter marker, angled two wide for the drive, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outkicked, while holding for third. BYE BYE BUGGSY was well placed in the early stages, tracked the decent pace from an inside position through the backstretch run, gained ground along the far turn and tipped two wide for the drive, was outrun by AIRKITA in upper stretch, could not muster a late response in deep stretch and was outfinished for third. COMPTONS HOUSE a bit slow into stride early on, was allowed to settle while outside of a rival, improved position two wide along the second turn, was roused three wide into the stretch and offered a mild late rally. HALLELUJAH BABY was unhurried, raced in the two path into the backstretch run then slipped to the rail approaching the far turn, gained ground nearing the quarter marker, could not sustain that run into the stretch, passed tired rivals in the late stages and did not factor. MANY MARKETS was prominent in the early running and disputed the pace into the first turn, contested the decent pace with AIRKITA through the backstretch run, chased that rival into the far turn, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the drive. RIVIERA SUNRISE settled in the second flight in the early stages, raced outside of rivals into the backstretch run, gained ground on the far turn while three wide and was steered four wide into the stretch, could not keep pace into the drive and tired in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUSKER ALLIE was unhurried in the early stages, steadied while in a bit tight entering the first turn, was coaxed along in the two path into the backstretch run, made a steady advance heading to the half-mile pole, continued that steady bid into the far turn and was roused three wide nearing the quarter marker, came within aim nearing mid-stretch, wore down foes inside of the furlong pole, took command approaching the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in deep stretch to prevail. CHEERFUL CHARM stalked the decent early pace while three deep on the first turn, was well placed through the backstretch run while on a snug hold, gained ground while three then two wide along the far turn, chased MISSING PENNY into the stretch, was outfinished by BUSKER ALLIE in the final stages and was second best. MISSING PENNY showed good early speed and dictated terms into the first turn, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, extended the lead along the far turn and drew to a clear lead into upper stretch, came under pressure nearing the furlong marker, was overtaken by BUSKER ALLIE approaching the sixteenth-pole, weakened in deep stretch and was outfinished for second, while just holding for third in the final strides. OAT MILK LATTE was crowded at the start and was off a step slowly, settled off of the early pace while outside of a rival, was carried out along the first turn and raced in the five path into the backstretch run, recovered and made up ground approaching the half-mile pole, raced two wide to the quarter marker, lost ground into upper stretch, lacked the needed response in the drive, finished evenly in the final stages and missed for third. BLUE BREEZE was allowed to settle, raced in the two path through the backstretch run, improved position heading to the half-mile marker, lost ground along the far turn, was steered three wide into the drive and did not threaten. HAPPY IS was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent pace while two wide into the backstretch run, kept attendance to the pacesetter to the half-mile pole, slipped to the rail entering the second turn, saved ground to the top of the stretch, could not keep pace into the drive and gave way. JAYS ANGEL broke alertly and was hustled to be prominent early on, stalked the decent pace from the inside through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground to the far turn, lost ground nearing the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the drive. JAZZY LOVE settled in the second flight in the early running, was hard to place along the first turn, bolted and carried out OAT MILK LATTE heading into the backstretch run, was pulled up nearing the five-furlong pole and walked off under her own power.

THREAD COUNT held up in a tracking position in the early going, stayed out in the three path for clear run, made a nice sweeping move through the turn, came into the stretch on the outside of a three horse fan contending for the lead, chased the eventual winner to the wire and was tagged at the wire for the place.
